Scholarship on college access

Demand-side causes and interventions

  • Research and policy discourse focuses on students and K-12 schools
    • e.g., 2014 White House Access Summit
  • The “under-matching” explanation
    • High-achieving, low-income students lack information/guidance
    • Interventions to overcome information asymmetries, nudge students

Sociology on recruiting

  • From the college perspective [CITE STEVENS]
    • High school visits important for relationships with prospects and counselors at “feeder” schools
  • From the student/high school perspective [CITE HOLLAND]
    • Which universities visit affects student decisions, especially first-generation and students of color
